Original message:

I first noticed this business years ago when I set up a website for a friend's forum. He was extremely appealed by the deal. After hosting with them for a very short time he parted ways.  At first I thought they were just another lowly shared host. Recently, I checked back to see how this web host innovated.

Instead of innovation, such as cloud architecture, exchange or inhouse solutions, they're making millions google bombing and spamming their homepage, and are one of the most prolific corporate spammers I've seen. By my estimates, they likely spent well-over 7 figures on blackhat SEO campaigns which earned the #1 result for hosting on Google search.

Further, They are Google bombing results like "Hostgator sucks" and "Hostgator scam" to bury criticism and constantly policing blogs for any critical comments. If it's a fraudulent bill, it was a mistake out of odds. If it's an ex-employee, they'll say it's a personal grudge over incompetence firing.

What is most despicable about this business is their management and lackey employees scour and attack people who have legitimate criticism of their business.

