There literally thousands more. They have spent 6 or 7 figs burying negative reviews, making them one of the top black hat spammers on the internet. This is pure blackhat SEO.  A sponsored conversation means Host gator paid bloggers to write a puff piece, see sites like https://payperpost.com/. Rarely do you see a legitimate client, out of 20 pages of sifting through hostgator ads, almost  9/10 of them were bought through ad services.

They will likely proffer it's by rogue affiliate advertisers. This is for the most part untrue - they're not even pretending to hide it with affiliate or referral links. They are that sloppy and obvious about it.

Hostgator even claims their own spam campaign speaks in their favor them:

"From the above number, only 1 out of every 10000 pages about HostGator says that this hosting sucks. This is still quite good considering other hosts we have looked at have way worst [sic] ratio.". 2010-10-28.
http://www.hostingsthatsuck.com/hostgator-sucks/
